  "body": "In preparation for a first release, here's a collection of todos needed for a minimal working chain. Add more items as they come up.\r\n\r\n### Documentation\r\n- [x] minimal tsdoc autogenerated docs #183 \r\n- [ ] separate docs page, make it pretty w/ :heart: \r\n- [ ] add a QA section in order to make sure that our instructions to run Lodestar are as clear and easy to understand as possible\r\n\r\n### Testing\r\n- [ ] pass ssz spec tests\r\n- [x] pass bls spec tests\r\n- [ ] pass state transition spec tests\r\n- [ ] unit tests for state transition utils\r\n\r\n### Benchmarking\r\n- [ ] add benchmarking framework\r\n- [ ] benchmark block processing\r\n- [ ] benchmark epoch processing\r\n- [ ] benchmark ssz\r\n- [ ] benchmark bls\r\n\r\n### Eth1\r\n- [ ] keep merkle tree of deposits #182 \r\n\r\n### Chain\r\n- [ ] unstub bls\r\n- [ ] feed attestations into fork choice\r\n- [ ] properly update state on fork choice decision\r\n- [ ] update FFG checkpoints on epoch end\r\n- [ ] perform any necessary cleanup after block processing ends\r\n\r\n### OpPool\r\n- [ ] unstub removal methods\r\n\r\n### Sync\r\n- [ ] initial sync\r\n- [ ] \"regular\" sync\r\n\r\n### Rpc\r\n- [ ] add health checks\r\n\r\n### Cli\r\n- [ ] add option for configuration file #177 \r\n\r\n### P2P\r\n- [ ] broadcast blocks\r\n- [ ] broadcast operations\r\n- [ ] follow [libp2p standardization](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/935), implement when ready\r\n- [ ] add browser-compatible libp2p node #170 \r\n- [ ] integrate [gossipsub](https://github.com/ChainSafe/gossipsub-js) when ready\r\n\r\n### Node\r\n- [ ] refactor as necessary for browser-specific node\r\n\r\n### Validator\r\n- [ ] unstub bls\r\n- [ ] unstub rpc client #188 \r\n- [ ] hook in attesting / block proposing logic\r\n- [ ] save attestations to disk - [ensure we're never slashed](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/validator/0_beacon-chain-validator.md#how-to-avoid-slashing)\r\n",
